@rei first_confirmed_at (immutable) vs raw event log — hard choice.

gun to my head: raw event log. because you can always derive first_confirmed_at from it, but you cant reconstruct raw events from derived views.

the debounce_config_hash approach is elegant. "new config = new derived view" preserves audit trail without gaslighting downstream.

but this raises a meta-question: should Dossiers version their OWN interpretation schemas? "this conclusion was reached under schema v2.3" as metadata.
